para_trans: Sant Sewalal Maharaj Banjara / Laman Tanda
The Zilla Parishad, Beed is headed by
Appointment of Non-Governmental Members to the Committee - 2
Government Decision No: Tansuyo-2024 / Q. No.29 (16) / Aastha-5
Government Decision No.: Department of Rural Development, No. Tanda Reforms-2019 / No.67 / Aastha-5,

Preamble: - Department of Rural Development, Government of India Decision No. Tanda Reforms-2019 / Q.67 / Aastha-5, D. Under the 23.02.2024, a committee has been constituted under the chairmanship of CEO, Zila Parishad to select the work to be done under Sant Sewalal Maharaj Banjara / Laman Tanda Samriddhi Yojana keeping in view the priority and urgency received from the Gram Panchayat and there is a provision to appoint 2 representatives of Banjara / Laman Samaj as non-official members in the said committee. However, since most Zila Parishads had administrators, it was seen necessary to appoint these non-official members from the government level. Considering this, the government was considering appointing non-governmental members in the committee headed by the CEO, Zilla Parishad, Beed for a period of 3 years from the government level.

Government Decision: - Keeping in view the priority and urgency of the work received from the Gram Panchayat under the Sant Sewalal Maharaj Banjara / Laman Tanda Samriddhi Yojana, 2 representatives of the Banjara / Laman community are being appointed as non-official members in the District Level Committee under the Chairmanship of CEO, Zila Parishad, Beed for a period of 3 years as follows.

Since the daily allowance and travel allowance payable to the said non-governmental members on the day of the meeting shall be paid from the 2 per cent of the fund admissible for the administrative expenses of the said scheme, the concerned non-governmental members shall submit the same to the CEO, Zila Parishad, Beed and the CEO, Zila Parishad, Beed shall pay the daily allowance to the concerned non-governmental members as per Government rules.
